The paper focuses on the performance of multicast routing protocols in mobile ad-hoc networks (MANET), which is a subfield of computer networks and falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of mobility models on the performance of these protocols, which involves analyzing and modeling data, making it relevant to the subfield of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves experimentation and evaluation of different protocols, which could fall under the subfield of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as these fields often involve experimentation and evaluation of algorithms and protocols.
